Time-activity curves (TACs) were obtained by defining relevant VOIs in the various anatomical regions of interest (Fig. 4), with the LVBP and AA defining IFs for the kinetic modelling. All TACs were obtained as the mean activity concentrations measured in the VOIs. The LVBP was defined in FOV-A using a limiting box and the hot-contour tool with a typical cutoff 45–60% of the maximum limiting box activity. Ensuring avoidance of surrounding activity in the right and left ventricular luminae, a background VOI was manually placed centrally in the left ventricular wall and defined on at least 10 contiguous slices. PVE and spill-over activity from the left ventricular wall was corrected adopting the method described by Katoh et al. [28]:
1RAt=β⋅CAt+1−β⋅ρ⋅CBgt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
